# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# QLDS UI — Docker Configuration
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. Copy this file:   cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in values below
# 3. Start:            docker compose up -d
# 4. First login:      admin/admin (or DEFAULT_ADMIN_USER/admin)
# 5. Change password:  required on first login

# ── Site Address ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Controls how the UI is accessed and whether HTTPS is enabled.
#
#   Automatic HTTPS (recommended for VPS with a domain):
#     SITE_ADDRESS=qlds.example.com
#     → Caddy obtains a free Let's Encrypt cert automatically.
#     → Your domain's A record must point to this server's IP.
#     → Ports 80 and 443 must be open.
#
#   HTTP only (home server, no domain):
#     SITE_ADDRESS=:80
#
#   Custom port:
#     SITE_ADDRESS=:8080
#
SITE_ADDRESS=:80

# ── Redis Password (required) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used to secure the Redis task queue. Generate a random value:
#   Linux/Mac: openssl rand -hex 16
#   Windows:   python -m secrets | python -c "import secrets;print(secrets.token_hex(16))"
REDIS_PASSWORD=

# ── Flask Secret Key (optional — auto-generated if not set) ──────────────────
# Signs JWT tokens and session cookies. Auto-generated on first run and stored
# in the qlds-data volume. Set manually if you need a stable key across installs.
#
# SECRET_KEY=

# ── Bootstrap Admin (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# On first run, QLDS UI creates one admin user automatically if the database
# has no users yet. The default login is admin/admin and the UI will require
# a password change immediately after login.
#
# Set this only if you want a different initial username.
#
# DEFAULT_ADMIN_USER=admin

# ── Cloud Provider (required for VM provisioning) ─────────────────────────────
# Required only if you want QLDS UI to provision Vultr VMs for you.
# Leave blank if you will add servers manually (standalone host mode).
# Get your key at: https://my.vultr.com/settings/#settingsapi
#
# VULTR_API_KEY=

# ── HTTPS Cookie Override ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to true if you have your own TLS-terminating proxy in front of Caddy
# and SITE_ADDRESS is set to a plain port like :80.
# In all other cases this is inferred automatically from SITE_ADDRESS.
#
# FORCE_HTTPS=false

# ── Grafana Password (optional — logging profile only) ────────────────────────
# Only used when starting with: docker compose --profile logging up -d
# Defaults to 'admin' if not set (change immediately after first login).
#
# GRAFANA_PASSWORD=

# ── Optional Tuning ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO          # DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR
# JWT_EXPIRATION_HOURS=24
